SIMPLE: litmus_test
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: litmus test
<hw>litmus test</hw>, <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A test to
determine acidity or alkalinity, using litmus as an
inddicator.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <mark>(Fig.)</mark> <def>A test
for a single factor, which has only two outcomes, positive or
negative;</def> <specif>specifically:</specif> <fld>(Politics)</fld>
<def>the question of whether a candidate for office is for or against a
particular position on an issue; -- used, e.g. by voters concerned
predominantly with a single issue, to decide whether to vote for or
against a candidate; <as>as, many voters take a candidate's position on
abortion as their <ex>litmus test</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Litocranius</ent>⟦br⟧
